messages.messagetext: Just over 260 miles done. Made it to Martin Rd. Got news yesterday that the Duluth section of the SHT is closed due to poor conditions so will be doing a re-route that stays as close to the trail as possible without going on the closed sections. While it felt devastating to find out that we wouldn’t be able to complete the trail as planned, and I have no clue whether it will count as “official”, we came out to have an adventure and what an adventure it has been.

At the 3 day mark, Alex reached Tettegouche, the approximate halfway point. Conditions are dicey, to say the least. Not just mud, but deep water covering sections of the trail. Lots of blown down trees covering the trail from Monday's storm. Also temps have dropped down below freezing overnight so boardwalks are icy, leaving her with no other choice but to crawl on her hands and knees across them. Just when you think you know what to expect. (photo credit: Tim Lupfer)
She finished up day 2 at Sawbill/Oberg late last night to complete the first 100 miles! Took a short nap then continued early early this morning.
Day 1 was filled with heavy rain and 50 mph winds. @aelizabethruns and her crew handled it like champs. Onto Day 2...
